energy.usef.agr.workflow.validate.create.dprognosis

Class AgrCreateDPrognosisPlanboardCoordinator

  • java.lang.Object
    • energy.usef.agr.workflow.validate.create.dprognosis.AgrCreateDPrognosisPlanboardCoordinator

  • public class AgrCreateDPrognosisPlanboardCoordinator
extends Object
    Aggregator coordinator class interacting with the planboard in the 'Create and Send D-Prognosis' workflow.

    No longer a Singleton, as this shall be executed per congestionPoint.

      • handleStartValidateEvent

        public void handleStartValidateEvent(@Observes
                                     StartValidateEvent event)
                              throws BusinessValidationException
        Handles a StartValidateEvent which contains the period for which D-Prognoses should be recreated.

        This triggers an ReCreateDPrognosisEvent which is handled by the handleReCreateDPrognosisEvent(energy.usef.agr.workflow.validate.create.dprognosis.ReCreateDPrognosisEvent).

        Parameters:
        event - StartValidateEvent.
        Throws:
        BusinessValidationException

      • handleReCreateDPrognosisEvent

        public void handleReCreateDPrognosisEvent(@Observes(during=AFTER_COMPLETION)
                                          ReCreateDPrognosisEvent event)
                                   throws BusinessValidationException
        Handles a ReCreateDPrognosisEvent which contains the period for which D-Prognoses should be recreated.

        For all D-Prognosis missing or flagged as 'TO_BE_RECREATED' in the database, the method will select the distinct congestion points and fire one CreateDPrognosisEvent per congestion point.

        Parameters:
        event -
        Throws:
        BusinessValidationException

      • handleEvent

        public void handleEvent(@Observes(during=AFTER_COMPLETION)
                        CreateDPrognosisEvent event)
                 throws BusinessValidationException
        Handles the CreateDPrognosisEvent. If the given period in the event is null, the period will be set to the current date. If the given congestion point in the event is null, prognoses will be created for every active congestion point.
        Parameters:
        event -
        Throws:
        BusinessValidationException
